---
import Section from "~/components/Section.astro";
import Stage from "~/components/Stage.astro";

// 4×4 grid standing in for an N₀=4, 2×2 hypercube.
// Target idx=6 → (i₀=2, b₁=0, b₂=1) in row-major flattening.
const cols = 4;
const rows = 4;
const targetCol = 2;
const targetRow = 1;
const cellW = 52;
const cellH = 34;
const gap = 8;
const gridX = 150;
const gridY = 80;
---

<Section id="onionpir-hypercube" num="05" title="OnionPIR — the hypercube">
  <p>
    <strong>OnionPIR</strong> is a single-server PIR scheme built on
    lattice-based homomorphic encryption. The textbook construction of
    homomorphic PIR — encrypt a one-hot selector vector
    <code>(Enc(0), …, Enc(1), …)</code> and let the server compute the
    inner product against the database — works in principle, but doesn't
    scale: the request grows linearly with the database. OnionPIR takes a
    different route, built around three ideas explored over the next three
    pages: reshape the database as a hypercube, mix two ciphertext
    flavors to walk it efficiently, and pack the whole query into a single
    ciphertext.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Reshape the database as a hypercube</strong> of shape
    <code>N<sub>0</sub> × 2 × 2 × … × 2</code>. The paper's standard setup
    uses <code>N<sub>0</sub> = 512</code> for the initial dimension, then
    <code>log<sub>2</sub>(N/N<sub>0</sub>)</code> binary dimensions (~11 of
    them for a 1 M-entry database). An index
    <code>idx</code> becomes a tuple
    <code>(i<sub>0</sub>, b<sub>1</sub>, …, b<sub>d−1</sub>)</code>:
    the initial dimension picks one of <code>N<sub>0</sub></code> columns,
    and each binary dimension is a single bit choosing top or bottom half of
    the remaining cube.
  </p>
  <p>
    That's the whole data-structuring move. The server walks the hypercube
    one axis at a time, collapsing it by one dimension at each step. The
    animation below shows the traversal as pure index arithmetic — no
    cryptography yet. The next page introduces the two ciphertext flavors
    that let the server do exactly this walk under encryption, without
    learning which column or which half was chosen.
  </p>

  <Stage
    caption="Index 6 decomposes into (i₀=2, b₁=0, b₂=1). The initial dim picks a column; each binary dim picks top or bottom half."
    label="Hypercube index traversal (plaintext)"
  >
    <svg viewBox="0 0 680 320" role="img"
      aria-label="A 4 by 4 grid representing an N0=4, 2×2 hypercube. Target index 6 is reached by picking column 2, then the top half, then the second row."
      data-anim="onion-cube">

      <!-- Grid label -->
      <text x={gridX + cols * (cellW + gap) / 2 - gap / 2} y={gridY - 42}
        text-anchor="middle" class="svg-label" font-size="11" font-weight="600"
        fill="var(--fg)">
        Database reshaped: 4 × 2 × 2 hypercube
      </text>
      <text x={gridX + cols * (cellW + gap) / 2 - gap / 2} y={gridY - 26}
        text-anchor="middle" class="svg-label" font-size="10">
        (the paper uses N₀ = 512 and ~11 binary dims; here, N₀ = 4, 2 binary dims)
      </text>

      <!-- 4×4 grid -->
      {Array.from({ length: rows }).map((_, r) =>
        Array.from({ length: cols }).map((__, c) => {
          const x = gridX + c * (cellW + gap);
          const y = gridY + r * (cellH + gap);
          const inCol = c === targetCol;
          const inHalf = r < 2;
          const isTarget = inCol && r === targetRow;
          const classes = [
            "cube-cell",
            inCol ? "col-sel" : "",
            inCol && inHalf ? "half-sel" : "",
            isTarget ? "final" : "",
          ].filter(Boolean).join(" ");
          return (
            <g class={classes}>
              <rect x={x} y={y} width={cellW} height={cellH} rx="4"
                class="cube-rect" fill="var(--bg-elev-2)"
                stroke="var(--border-strong)" stroke-width="1"/>
              <text x={x + cellW / 2} y={y + cellH / 2 + 4}
                text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" class="svg-label"
                font-family="ui-monospace, monospace">
                {r * cols + c}
              </text>
            </g>
          );
        })
      )}

      <!-- Axis labels -->
      <text x={gridX - 12} y={gridY + rows * (cellH + gap) / 2}
        text-anchor="end" class="svg-label" font-size="10">
        dims 1–2 ↕
      </text>
      <text x={gridX + cols * (cellW + gap) / 2 - gap / 2}
        y={gridY + rows * (cellH + gap) + 16}
        text-anchor="middle" class="svg-label" font-size="10">
        dim 0 (initial) →
      </text>

      <!-- Tuple builder on right -->
      <g transform="translate(440,90)">
        <text x="0" y="0" class="svg-label" font-size="11" font-weight="600"
          fill="var(--fg)">idx = 6</text>
        <text x="0" y="18" class="svg-label" font-size="10">
          ↓ decompose into tuple
        </text>
        <g transform="translate(0,36)" class="tup tup-a">
          <rect width="180" height="22" rx="4" fill="var(--accent)" opacity="0.2" stroke="var(--accent)"/>
          <text x="90" y="15" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" fill="var(--accent)" font-weight="700">
            i₀ = 2  (pick column)
          </text>
        </g>
        <g transform="translate(0,66)" class="tup tup-b">
          <rect width="180" height="22" rx="4" fill="#e8a33c" opacity="0.25" stroke="#e8a33c"/>
          <text x="90" y="15" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" fill="#e8a33c" font-weight="700">
            b₁ = 0  (top half)
          </text>
        </g>
        <g transform="translate(0,96)" class="tup tup-c">
          <rect width="180" height="22" rx="4" fill="#e8a33c" opacity="0.25" stroke="#e8a33c"/>
          <text x="90" y="15" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" fill="#e8a33c" font-weight="700">
            b₂ = 1  (bottom of that half)
          </text>
        </g>
        <g transform="translate(0,130)" class="tup tup-d">
          <rect width="180" height="22" rx="4" fill="var(--ok)" opacity="0.2" stroke="var(--ok)"/>
          <text x="90" y="15" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" fill="var(--ok)" font-weight="700">
            → entry at (2, 0, 1)
          </text>
        </g>
      </g>
    </svg>
  </Stage>
</Section>

<style>
  [data-anim="onion-cube"] .tup { opacity: 0; }
  [data-anim="onion-cube"] .cube-cell { transition: opacity 0.4s; }

  [data-anim="onion-cube"].play .cube-cell:not(.col-sel) {
    animation: cube-dim 0.5s var(--ease) 1.0s forwards;
  }
  [data-anim="onion-cube"].play .tup-a {
    animation: cube-in 0.4s var(--ease) 1.0s forwards;
  }

  [data-anim="onion-cube"].play .col-sel:not(.half-sel) {
    animation: cube-dim 0.5s var(--ease) 2.0s forwards;
  }
  [data-anim="onion-cube"].play .tup-b {
    animation: cube-in 0.4s var(--ease) 2.0s forwards;
  }

  [data-anim="onion-cube"].play .half-sel:not(.final) {
    animation: cube-dim 0.5s var(--ease) 3.0s forwards;
  }
  [data-anim="onion-cube"].play .tup-c {
    animation: cube-in 0.4s var(--ease) 3.0s forwards;
  }

  [data-anim="onion-cube"].play .final .cube-rect {
    animation: cube-glow 0.6s var(--ease) 3.4s forwards;
  }
  [data-anim="onion-cube"].play .tup-d {
    animation: cube-in 0.5s var(--ease) 3.8s forwards;
  }

  @keyframes cube-in { to { opacity: 1; } }
  @keyframes cube-dim { to { opacity: 0.15; } }
  @keyframes cube-glow { to { fill: var(--ok); } }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    [data-anim="onion-cube"] .tup { opacity: 1 !important; }
    [data-anim="onion-cube"] .cube-cell:not(.col-sel) { opacity: 0.15 !important; }
    [data-anim="onion-cube"] .col-sel:not(.half-sel) { opacity: 0.15 !important; }
    [data-anim="onion-cube"] .half-sel:not(.final) { opacity: 0.15 !important; }
    [data-anim="onion-cube"] .final .cube-rect { fill: var(--ok) !important; }
  }
</style>

<script is:inline>
  document.querySelectorAll('[data-anim="onion-cube"]').forEach((svg) => {
    const stage = svg.closest("[data-stage]");
    const run = () => {
      svg.classList.remove("play");
      void svg.getBoundingClientRect();
      svg.classList.add("play");
    };
    stage?.addEventListener("stage:visible", run);
    svg.addEventListener("click", run);
  });
</script>
